page.title: 12NATURAL HISTORY
page.content: Close to my home are some woods.When you walk through them you can see many interesting things.There are foxgloves, harebells, dog daisies, speedwell, buttercups, violets, daisies and stitchwort.These flowers grow in the clearings between the trees.Most of the trees are rowans, silver birch, ash or sycamore but there are some larch and pine trees too. The trees often have fungi growing on them in the autumn. If you are quiet,you may see rabbits, squirrels, or even stoats in the wood. Magpies, jays, blue tits, great tits, wood pigeons and blackbirds fly about overhead and on the small pond you can see mallards and moorhens. There are patches of bracken that are fun to hide in and also bilberry and blackberry bushes that aren't.
